article.description: — Gabe McGlothan had 20 points in Grand Canyon's 74-48 win against Tarleton State on Saturday night.
article.headline: McGlothan scores 20 lead Grand Canyon over Tarleton State 74-48
article.linkText: McGlothan scores 20 lead Grand Canyon over Tarleton State 74-48
article.story: PHOENIX -- — Gabe McGlothan had 20 points in Grand Canyon's 74-48 win against Tarleton State on Saturday night. McGlothan also contributed nine rebounds for the Antelopes (16-1, 6-0 Western Athletic Conference). Tyon Grant-Foster scored 16 points and added seven rebounds and three blocks. Rayshon Harrison went 4 of 6 from the field to finish with nine points. The Antelopes picked up their 13th straight win. The Texans (10-6, 3-2) were led in scoring by Devon Barnes, who finished with 11 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
